### C# Feature Support for Conversion

Most C# features convert cleanly to Calor. Key supported features include:

**Fully supported**: classes, structs, interfaces, enums, records, abstract/sealed/static classes, generics (including nested/constrained), inheritance, properties (auto/computed/init), fields, constructors (with base/this chains), methods (virtual/override/abstract/async), operators (including implicit/explicit conversion), indexers, events, delegates, lambdas, LINQ, pattern matching (type/constant/relational/logical and/or/not/var/discard/tuple/positional patterns), switch expressions, nullable types, string interpolation, collection expressions, goto/label, yield return/break, throw expressions, lock, stackalloc, volatile, extension methods, using declarations, with expressions, required members, primary constructors, range/index expressions, null-coalescing/null-conditional, tuples, named arguments, attributes.

**Partial support** (most usage converts): is-pattern with complex recursion, implicit `new()` with arguments, checked/unchecked blocks (wrapper stripped, body preserved), ref/out parameters, dynamic types, generic method expressions.

**Not yet supported**: list/slice patterns (`[a, ..rest]`), `ref struct`, `static abstract` interface members, `in` parameters, mixed collection spread (`[1, ..other]`), `await foreach`/`await using`.

Use `calor_feature_support` to check specific features, or `calor_batch_analyze` to assess an entire project.

### Quick Syntax Reference

| Structure | Calor Syntax |
|-----------|-------------|
| Module | `§M{id:Name}` ... `§/M{id}` |
| Function | `§F{id:name:returnType:vis}` ... `§/F{id}` |
| Binding | `§B{name:type} expr` (immutable), `§B{~name:type}` (mutable) |
| Loop | `§L{id:var:from:to:step}` ... `§/L{id}` |
| Conditional | `§IF{id} (cond) → §R expr` |
| Contracts | `§Q (precondition)`, `§S (postcondition)` |
| Types | `i32`, `i64`, `str`, `bool`, `f64`, `void`, `?i32` (option), `i32!str` (result) |
| Expressions | Prefix notation: `(+ a b)`, `(== x 0)`, `(% i 15)` |
| Literals | `INT:42`, `STR:"hello"`, `BOOL:true`, `FLOAT:3.14` |

